  "root_text": {
    "an8.60:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8.60 ",
    "an8.60:0.2": "6. Gotamīvagga ",
    "an8.60:0.3": "Dutiyapuggalasutta ",
    "an8.60:1.1": "“Aṭṭhime, bhikkhave, puggalā āhuneyyā …pe… anuttaraṁ puññakkhettaṁ lokassa. ",
    "an8.60:1.2": "Katame aṭṭha? ",
    "an8.60:1.3": "Sotāpanno, sotāpattiphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanno …pe… arahā, arahattāya paṭipanno. ",
    "an8.60:1.4": "Ime kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭha puggalā āhuneyyā …pe… anuttaraṁ puññakkhettaṁ lokassāti. ",
    "an8.60:2.1": "Cattāro ca paṭipannā, ",
    "an8.60:2.2": "cattāro ca phale ṭhitā; ",
    "an8.60:2.3": "Esa saṅgho samukkaṭṭho, ",
    "an8.60:2.4": "sattānaṁ aṭṭha puggalā. ",
    "an8.60:3.1": "Yajamānānaṁ manussānaṁ, ",
    "an8.60:3.2": "puññapekkhāna pāṇinaṁ; ",
    "an8.60:3.3": "Karotaṁ opadhikaṁ puññaṁ, ",
    "an8.60:3.4": "ettha dinnaṁ mahapphalan”ti. ",
    "an8.60:3.5": "Dasamaṁ. ",
    "an8.60:3.6": "Gotamīvaggo paṭhamo. ",
    "an8.60:4.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "an8.60:4.1": "Gotamī ovādaṁ saṅkhittaṁ, ",
    "an8.60:4.2": "dīghajāṇu ca ujjayo; ",
    "an8.60:4.3": "Bhayā dve āhuneyyā ca, ",
    "an8.60:4.4": "dve ca aṭṭha puggalāti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an8.60:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 8.60 ",
    "an8.60:0.2": "6. Gotamī ",
    "an8.60:0.3": "Eight Individuals (2nd) ",
    "an8.60:1.1": "“Mendicants, these eight individuals are worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of greeting with joined palms, and are the supreme field of merit for the world. ",
    "an8.60:1.2": "What eight? ",
    "an8.60:1.3": "The stream-enterer and the one practicing to realize the fruit of stream-entry. The once-returner and the one practicing to realize the fruit of once-return. The non-returner and the one practicing to realize the fruit of non-return. The perfected one, and the one practicing for perfection. ",
    "an8.60:1.4": "These are the eight individuals who are worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of greeting with joined palms, and are the supreme field of merit for the world. ",
    "an8.60:2.1": "Four practicing the path, ",
    "an8.60:2.2": "and four established in the fruit. ",
    "an8.60:2.3": "This is the exalted Saṅgha, ",
    "an8.60:2.4": "the eight individuals among sentient beings. ",
    "an8.60:3.1": "For humans, those merit-seeking creatures, ",
    "an8.60:3.2": "who sponsor sacrifices, ",
    "an8.60:3.3": "making worldly merit, ",
    "an8.60:3.4": "what’s given here is very fruitful.” ",
